"{\"correct\": \"no\", \"explanation\": \"The np.sinc function expects the input to be in radians, but the input provided is in the form of integers. The expected behavior is that np.sinc(x) computes sin(pi * x) / (pi * x), which means the input should be multiplied by pi to get the correct results.\", \"patch\": \"5c5\\n< sinc_result = np.sinc(original_data)\\n---\\n> sinc_result = np.sinc(original_data * np.pi)\"}"